00:16:38,780 --> 00:16:40,630
but it speaks to something bigger.

494
00:16:40,710 --> 00:16:42,320
I don't know if I can spend the rest of my life

495
00:16:42,320 --> 00:16:44,510
with the kind of guy who won't let me eat off his plate.

496
00:16:44,510 --> 00:16:45,880
Trust me -- it can be done.

497
00:16:45,890 --> 00:16:48,360
And I should not make such a big deal about that.

498
00:16:48,360 --> 00:16:49,670
I promise I'll try and do better.

499
00:16:49,670 --> 00:16:51,170
No, you're right. You don't like it,

500
00:16:51,170 --> 00:16:53,030
and I should respect that more.

501
00:16:53,030 --> 00:16:53,780
Are you guys married?

502
00:16:53,780 --> 00:16:54,880
Oh, this May.

503
00:16:54,880 --> 00:16:58,250
- But, basically, we've been married for years. - Yeah.

504
00:16:58,250 --> 00:17:00,530
I-I mean, is Cam everything that I dreamed of?

505
00:17:00,530 --> 00:17:01,580
Tread lightly, counselor.

506
00:17:01,580 --> 00:17:03,780
Yes. Yes, he is.

507
00:17:03,790 --> 00:17:05,450
Because through all the compromises

508
00:17:05,450 --> 00:17:07,200
and negotiations and arguments

509
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:08,850
and sometimes even boredom,

510
00:17:08,850 --> 00:17:11,620
I cannot picture my life without him.

511
00:17:11,620 --> 00:17:12,190
That's very sweet.

512
00:17:12,190 --> 00:17:13,760
I would've scooted past the boredom, but...

513
00:17:13,760 --> 00:17:16,300
At the end of the day, Katie, you have to ask yourself,

514
00:17:16,300 --> 00:17:18,820
can you imagine your life without this person?

515
00:17:20,650 --> 00:17:21,720
Hey. All right, look.

516
00:17:21,730 --> 00:17:23,990
I, uh, paid the check, okay? Let's just go.

517
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:25,590
Brandon, can you just please sit?

518
00:17:25,590 --> 00:17:26,730
I've been talking to the guys here,

519
00:17:26,730 --> 00:17:29,170
and they really opened my eyes.

520
00:17:29,820 --> 00:17:30,480
They did?

521
00:17:30,480 --> 00:17:31,400
Yes.

522
00:17:31,530 --> 00:17:35,160
I've been trying to picture my life without you, and...

523
00:17:35,540 --> 00:17:36,460
You know what?

524
00:17:37,260 --> 00:17:38,410
I can.

525
00:17:39,160 --> 00:17:40,100
We didn't tell her that.

526
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:40,850
I didn't say that.

527
00:17:40,850 --> 00:17:43,170
No, I want what you guys have, okay?

528
00:17:43,180 --> 00:17:44,730
I'm sorry, Brandon.

529
00:17:44,730 --> 00:17:47,280
I am so sorry, but we both deserve that.

530
00:17:47,280 --> 00:17:49,750
I've never been so sure of anything.

531
00:17:51,030 --> 00:17:51,990
You know what? I'm just...

532
00:17:51,990 --> 00:17:53,740
gonna go get a cab, okay?

533
00:17:54,370 --> 00:17:55,150
Goodbye.

534
00:17:55,150 --> 00:17:56,670
And thank you.

535
00:17:56,670 --> 00:17:58,570
- Don't-- don't thank us! - We didn't do anything,

536
00:17:58,570 --> 00:18:00,320
So... we didn't, honestly.

537
00:18:00,320 --> 00:18:02,070
This is the worst night of my life.

538
00:18:02,070 --> 00:18:02,980
I'm sorry.

539
00:18:03,460 --> 00:18:06,130
But, I mean, um, a-at least now it's over.

540
00:18:06,130 --> 00:18:08,410
You can... start to move on.

541
00:18:08,640 --> 00:18:11,530
I've been trying to picture my life without you.

542
00:18:11,530 --> 00:18:13,540
And you know what?

543
00:18:13,590 --> 00:18:15,210
- S-stupid phone. - I can.

544
00:18:15,220 --> 00:18:18,310
It's a... devil phone.

545
00:18:21,330 --> 00:18:24,090
When Mitchell was born, he was a month premature.

546
00:18:24,090 --> 00:18:26,610
So it was touch and go there for a while.

547
00:18:26,890 --> 00:18:27,950
It's 2 a.m.

548
00:18:27,960 --> 00:18:30,950
I walk out into the hospital waiting room to get some air,

549
00:18:31,430 --> 00:18:32,710
and there's Shorty.

550
00:18:33,540 --> 00:18:35,360
He'd been sitting there for six hours

551
00:18:35,360 --> 00:18:37,980
and refused to leave for the next two days.

552
00:18:38,230 --> 00:18:39,980
That's where we got Mitchell's middle name.

553
00:18:39,980 --> 00:18:41,190
Not Shorty --

554
00:18:41,550 --> 00:18:42,570
Vincent.

555
00:18:43,120 --> 00:18:44,650
"M.V.P."

556
00:18:45,820 --> 00:18:48,000
We were a little premature on that one, too.

557
00:18:50,660 --> 00:18:52,540
Gloria, I'm going for a drive!

558
00:18:52,820 --> 00:18:54,050
Say hi to Shorty for me!

559
00:18:54,050 --> 00:18:55,410
I'm not talking to you!

560
00:19:00,750 --> 00:19:02,220
I was just coming to see you.

561
00:19:02,550 --> 00:19:04,300
Um, I left my jacket.

562
00:19:04,300 --> 00:19:06,890
Oh! There it is! Come on in.

563
00:19:12,390 --> 00:19:14,020
Uh, Shorty, you know that stuff I said, uh --

564
00:19:14,020 --> 00:19:16,080
- Yeah, I get it. - We're good, huh?

565
00:19:16,080 --> 00:19:17,190
Under the bridge.

566
00:19:18,930 --> 00:19:20,000
All right. I'll see you.

567
00:19:20,010 --> 00:19:21,190
Shorty, wait.

568
00:19:23,010 --> 00:19:24,310
I need to say something to you.

569
00:19:24,310 --> 00:19:25,280
Yeah.

570
00:19:26,670 --> 00:19:28,280
I want to thank you...

571
00:19:28,870 --> 00:19:30,810
for all the great times we've had.

572
00:19:31,700 --> 00:19:33,620
Yeah. We, um...

573
00:19:34,420 --> 00:19:36,110
- We had a lot of laughs. - Yeah.

574
00:19:36,920 --> 00:19:38,590
And you should know that, uh...

575
00:19:39,490 --> 00:19:40,750
you're my best friend.

576
00:19:41,640 --> 00:19:42,590
You know?

577
00:19:43,170 --> 00:19:45,330
Probably the best friend I'm ever gonna have.

578
00:19:45,340 --> 00:19:47,460
Jay, I mean... what are you doing to me?

579
00:19:47,460 --> 00:19:49,100
This is hard for me. I'm just...

580
00:19:49,620 --> 00:19:51,540
I'm just trying to tell you how I feel.

581
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:53,740
Well, I'm gonna tell you how I feel.

582
00:19:54,900 --> 00:19:57,000
I admire the hell out of you, Jay.

583
00:19:57,560 --> 00:20:00,330
I always tell Darlene, "That's a real guy."

584
00:20:00,330 --> 00:20:02,260
Self-made, stand-up,

585
00:20:02,840 --> 00:20:04,860
the kind of guy you want to be in a foxhole with.

586
00:20:04,860 --> 00:20:06,180
Well, I'm not all that.

587
00:20:06,180 --> 00:20:08,090
Well, it's not like I've been in a foxhole.

588
00:20:12,710 --> 00:20:14,330
I'm gonna miss you, Vincent.

589
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:16,170
I'm gonna miss you, too.

590
00:20:16,290 --> 00:20:17,310
I love you.

591
00:20:18,890 --> 00:20:20,500
I love you, too, Jay bird.

592
00:20:20,610 --> 00:20:22,080
I really, really do.

593
00:20:26,830 --> 00:20:27,650
You call me, okay?

594
00:20:27,650 --> 00:20:28,710
Every day.

595
00:20:29,870 --> 00:20:31,400
Every damn day.

596
00:20:33,070 --> 00:20:34,360
If I'm being honest,

597
00:20:34,360 --> 00:20:36,440
this is a little girlier than I thought.

598
00:20:42,280 --> 00:20:43,470
Two years.

599
00:20:44,570 --> 00:20:46,100
How could she just walk away?

600
00:20:46,100 --> 00:20:47,930
- You know what? She did you a favor. - Absolutely.

601
00:20:47,930 --> 00:20:50,810
- You can do so much better. - Oh, my god. Insanely better.

602
00:20:50,810 --> 00:20:54,140
No, he's not kidding. Brandon, you are seriously gorge!

603
00:20:54,140 --> 00:20:56,140
If you ask me, she got the better end of the deal.

604
00:20:56,150 --> 00:20:56,970
You really think so?

605
00:20:56,970 --> 00:20:58,320
- Yes! Yes! - Yes!

606
00:20:58,320 --> 00:21:00,110
And her whole fake blond thing? I don't know.

607
00:21:00,110 --> 00:21:01,330
- It was kind of trampy. - And truth be told,

608
00:21:01,340 --> 00:21:02,650
she didn't seem that bright.

609
00:21:02,650 --> 00:21:03,800
And is she older than you?

610
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:06,460
- Because she looked significantly older than you. - Trust us.

611
00:21:06,460 --> 00:21:07,040
This is the best thing that's ever happened to you.

612
00:21:07,040 --> 00:21:09,440
Best thing that's ever happened to you.

613
00:21:09,440 --> 00:21:11,260
Oh! Thank god you're still here!

614
00:21:11,260 --> 00:21:13,980
I was on my way home, and all of a sudden, I started crying.

615
00:21:13,980 --> 00:21:15,370
And I realized I was just scared.

616
00:21:15,370 --> 00:21:18,240
And I love you. And I'm so, so sorry.

617
00:21:18,240 --> 00:21:20,610
And, yes, Brandon, if you'll still have me,

618
00:21:20,610 --> 00:21:22,900
Yes, I will marry you!

619
00:21:24,700 --> 00:21:26,660
- So nice meeting you. - Okay.

